article.headline: Winthrop 68, Liberty 40
article.story: LYNCHBURG, Va. (AP) -- Craig Bradshaw had 16 points to lead Winthrop to a 68-40 win over Liberty on Saturday night The Eagles (13-4, 3-0 Big South) went on a 9-2 run early in the first and used a 15-5 run to go into the second half up 39-15. The Flames (7-10, 1-2) trailed the whole game, tying the game once in the opening minutes of the first period. Liberty started the second with a 7-3 run to cut Winthrop's lead to 42-22 with 17 minutes to play, but the Eagles answered back with a 9-3 run to make it 58-27 with 8:53 left. Winthrop, which had its largest lead of 33 with 5:20 to play, had 51 percent shooting for the game and kept the Flames to 28.6 percent from the field. The Eagles also outrebounded Liberty 48-30. Michael Jenkins added 15 for the Eagles and Taj McCullough had 11. Larry Blair led Liberty with 13 points.
